**Algorithm for C**
* Create a separate index starting at 0 and insert non-zero num in nums array. And increment index.
* Insert 0 at the remaining spaces left
* Time Complexity: O(n) | Space Complexity: O(1)

**Code for C**
```
void moveZeroes(int* nums, int numsSize){
    int index = 0;
    for(int i=0; i<numsSize; i++){
        if(nums[i] != 0){
            nums[index] = nums[i]; index++;
        }
    }
    for(int i=index; i<numsSize; i++){
        nums[i] = 0;
    }
}
```

**Algorithm for Java**
* Insert non-zero element in HashMap.
* Insert all the values of HashMap in nums.
* Insert zero at the remaining spaces left.
* Time Complexity: O(n) | Space Complexity: O(n)

**Code for Java**


```
public void moveZeroes(int[] nums) {
        Map<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap();
        int index=0;
        for(int i=0; i<nums.length; i++){
            if(nums[i] != 0) {
                map.put(index, nums[i]);
                index++;
            }
        }
        int i=0;
        for(Map.Entry<Integer, Integer> temp : map.entrySet()){
            nums[i] = temp.getValue(); i++;
        }
        for(int k = i; k<nums.length; k++){
            nums[k] = 0;
        }
    }
```

