Given value = v, This question is to find integers b & n that

v = 1 + b + b^2 + b^3 + ... + b^n

with n is maximized. (so that b will be mininized)

Clearly every number v has a pair (b, n) = (v-1, 1) that v = 1 + (v-1)
Thus b1 = v-1.

So my solution will add possible basis  (b1, ..., bn) in ans and output the last one

To find bm, with m >= 2
Of course we need to compute the polynomial of 1+b+b^2+b^3 + ... + b^m
=> write method " long poly(long b, int n) " returns its sum

We loop on n = 2 ~ 62 (maybe 62 is loose bound)
We use n^2 <= v = 1+x+x^2 <= (n+1)^2 to find n
We directly take rm = y^(1/m). 
and its value bm will be around  [y^(1/m) -2 , y^(1/m) + 2] (No take on binary search)
we check for valid for v-1 = x * (1+x+...+x^m-1) with modular and add the candidate to ans if 
v = 1+b+b^2+..+b^m meets

```
class Solution {
    // 2020/05/08 18:46
    public String smallestGoodBase(String n) {
        return sol1(n);
    }

    private String sol1(String n) {
        long x = Long.parseLong(n);
        List<Long> ans = new ArrayList<>();
        ans.add(x-1);
        long y = x-1;
        for (int i = 2; i < 63; i++) {
            double dm = Math.pow(y, 1.0 / i);
            long dml = (long) dm;
            //ln("dml = %s, dm = %s", dml, dm);
            for (int j = 0; j > -3 && dml + j > 1; j--) {
                long d = dml + j;
                if (y % d == 0) {
                    long poly = poly(d, i);
                    //ln("possible %s, %s", d, poly);
                    if (poly == x) {
                        //ln("hi, poly %s, %s", x, poly);
                        ans.add(d);
                    }
                }
            }
            //ln("#%s : ans = %s", i, ans);
        }
        //ln("ans = %s", ans);
        long end = ans.get(ans.size() - 1);
        return end+"";
        //return n;
    }

    // return 1+b+b^2+...+b^n;
    long poly(long b, int n) {
        long ans = 1;
        long m = 1;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            m *= b;
            ans += m;
        }
        return ans;
    }

    void ln(String f, Object... p) {
        System.out.println((p == null) ? f : String.format(f, p));
    }
}
