Approach :-
We can use LCS here to find out the largest common sequence between the Strings 
then  we Subtract this LCS count form both s1 string length and s2 string length
i.e - m + n - (2 * LCS) 
example :
```
s1 -> " a b c d e g"   m-> 6
s2 -> " k b c p d  "    n-> 5

here the lcs for both the string is  "b c d" length of the lcs is 3 
 So the number of operation = m + n - (2 * LCS) = 6 + 5 - 6 = 5;
 1 -> a
 2 -> e
 3 -> g
 4 -> k
 5 -> p
 so after removing this element we will get our answer "b c d"


```


 #### Please vote up if you like the solution 
Here is my  from Recurisive to best optimal solution 
#### 1.Recursive Solution (Gives TLE)
##### Time Complexity - exponential time 
##### Space - Recursive Stack space 
```
public int minDistance(String word1, String word2) {
        int m = word1.length();
        int n = word2.length();
        int lcs = LCS(word1,word2,m,n);  
        return m+n-(2*lcs);
    }
    private static int LCS(String s1,String s2,int m,int n,){
        if(n==0 || m==0) return 0;
        if(s1.charAt(m-1) == s2.charAt(n-1)){
            return 1+LCS(s1,s2,m-1,n-1);
        }
        else
            return Math.max(LCS(s1,s2,m-1,n),LCS(s1,s2,m,n-1));
    }
```
##### 2. Memoization DP 
##### Time Complexity - O(m*n)
##### Space - Recursive Stack space + O(m*n) 
```
public int minDistance(String word1, String word2) {
        int m = word1.length();
        int n = word2.length();

        int[][] dp = new int[m+1][n+1];
        for(int[] d: dp) Arrays.fill(d,-1);

        int lcs = LCS(word1,word2,m,n,dp);
        return m+n-(2*lcs);
    }
    private static int LCS(String s1,String s2,int m,int n,int[][] dp){
        if(n==0 || m==0) return 0;
        if(dp[m][n] != -1) return dp[m][n];

        if(s1.charAt(m-1) == s2.charAt(n-1))
            return dp[m][n] = 1+LCS(s1,s2,m-1,n-1,dp);

        else
            return dp[m][n] = Math.max(LCS(s1,s2,m-1,n,dp),LCS(s1,s2,m,n-1,dp));
    }
```
#### 3. BUttom up Dp 
##### Time Complexity - O(m*n)
##### Space - O(m*n) 
```
public int minDistance(String word1, String word2) {
        int m = word1.length();
        int n = word2.length();

        int[][] dp = new int[m+1][n+1];
        // as java already contain 0 as default value no need to initailize the dp array
        for(int i = 1 ; i < m+1 ;i++){
            for(int j = 1 ; j < n+1 ; j++){
                if(word1.charAt(i-1) == word2.charAt(j-1))
                     dp[i][j] = 1+dp[i-1][j-1];

                 else
                     dp[i][j] = Math.max(dp[i-1][j] , dp[i][j-1]);       
            }
        }
         return m+n-(2*dp[m][n]);
     }
```
