solutions.content:
This is easy-medium DP problem. IT is somewhat similar like LCS,, we can use LCS to find longest common substring and then simply return 
```   s1.size() + s2.size() - 2*(length of longest common substring)```

Here in the below solution we store answer till (i-1)th index of word1 and (j-1)th index of word2 in dp[i][j].
If (i-1)th character matches with (j-1)th character the answer if same as of till (i-2)th & (j-2)th character which we had earlier store into dp[i-1][j-1].
AND if character doesn't matches we delete curr character from both strings one by one and and take the min of both the answers and simply add 1 to it(as we are deleting curr character)...

**Time and Space Comlexity** : s1.size()*s2.size() 
```
 int minDistance(string word1, string word2) {
        int n=word1.size();
        int m=word2.size();
        vector<vector<int>>dp(n+1,vector<int>(m+1));
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){   // if  word2 is empty then the answer is surely the length of word1
            dp[i][0]=i;     
        }
        for(int j=1;j<=m;j++){    
            dp[0][j]=j;               // if word1 is empty then the answer is surely the length of word2
        }
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<=m;j++){
                if(word1[i-1]==word2[j-1]){       // if current characters ((i-1)th and (j-1)th) matches then we dont have to delete any 
                    dp[i][j]=dp[i-1][j-1];               //  character from either of the string so the answer is same as dp[i-1][j-1]
                }else{    // if characters dont matches then we had to delete one character but here we have options either to delete from word1 or word 2
                    dp[i][j]=min(dp[i-1][j],dp[i][j-1])+1; // so we add 1 as we are deleting one charater and take min of both the options (dp[i-1][j],if delete from word1,,dp[i])[j-1]:if delete from word2)
                }
            }
        }
        return dp[n][m];
    }

```

