solutions.content:
__NAIVE | MEMOIZED | TABULATION | SPACE OPTIMIZED__
* This problem is similar to LCS and Edit distance questions.
* Problem is simple and clear, that we have to delete a character in either of the strings to make same if characters are not same, if same remove both.
* That is what we exacty do and return min of these results.
* Coming to base case, assume we a string of length N and another string of length 0.
* Now to convert from one stirng to another, we exactly need N characters to delete.
* That is what we return in base case, cleverly summing m & n.

* __NAIVE RECURSIVE APPROACH__
```
    private int solve(String s, String t, int m, int n){

        if(m == 0 || n == 0) return  m + n;

        if(s.charAt(m - 1) == t.charAt(n - 1)) 
            return solve(s, t, m - 1, n - 1);

        int deleteInS = solve(s, t, m - 1, n);
        int deleteInT = solve(s, t, m, n - 1);

        return Math.min(deleteInS, deleteInT) + 1;
    }
```

* __MEMOIZED APPROACH__
```
    private int solve(String s, String t, int m, int n, int[][] dp){

        if(m == 0 || n == 0) return dp[m][n] = m + n;

        if(dp[m][n] != -1) return dp[m][n];

        if(s.charAt(m - 1) == t.charAt(n - 1)) 
            return solve(s, t, m - 1, n - 1, dp);

        int deleteInS = solve(s, t, m - 1, n, dp);
        int deleteInT = solve(s, t, m, n - 1, dp);

        return dp[m][n] = Math.min(deleteInS, deleteInT) + 1;
    }
```

* __TABULATION__
```
    public int minDistance(String s, String t) {

        int m = s.length(), n = t.length();
        int[][] dp = new int[m + 1][n + 1];
        for(int[] row : dp) Arrays.fill(row, -1);

        for(int i = 0; i <= m; i++)
            dp[i][0] = i;

        for(int j = 0; j <= n; j++)
            dp[0][j] = j;

        for(int i = 1; i <= m; i++){
            for(int j = 1; j <= n; j++){
                if(s.charAt(i - 1) == t.charAt(j - 1))
                    dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j - 1];
                else{
                    int deleteInS = dp[i - 1][j];
                    int deleteInT = dp[i][j - 1];
                    dp[i][j] = Math.min(deleteInS, deleteInT) + 1;
                }
            }
        }

        return dp[m][n];
    }
```

* __SPACE OPTIMIZED 1D ARRAY__
```
class Solution {

    public int minDistance(String s, String t) {

        int m = s.length(), n = t.length();
        int[] dp = new int[n + 1];

        for(int j = 0; j <= n; j++) dp[j] = j;


        for(int i = 1; i <= m; i++){
            int[] curr = new int[n + 1];
            curr[0] = i;

            for(int j = 1; j <= n; j++){
                if(s.charAt(i - 1) == t.charAt(j - 1)){
                    curr[j] = dp[j - 1];
                } else {
                    int deleteInS = dp[j];
                    int deleteInT = curr[j - 1];
                    curr[j] = Math.min(deleteInS, deleteInT) + 1;
                }
            }
            dp = curr;
        }
        return dp[n];
    }
}
```

