According to question, we have to find minimum number steps require to make both string same by deleting exactly one character in one of the string at a time.
Intution : If we find the largest common string (subsequence not substring because we want minimum deletion of characters) then the deletion is minimum. So, If we find longest common subsequence (LCS) and then word1.size-lcs + word2.size-lcs is our answer.

Approach 1: Recursion
TC: O(2^max(n,m))

```
class Solution {
public:
    int lcs(string s1,string s2,int n,int m){
        if(n<0 || m<0)
            return 0;
        if(s1[n]==s2[m])
            return 1+lcs(s1,s2,n-1,m-1);
        else
            return max(lcs(s1,s2,n-1,m),lcs(s1,s2,n,m-1));
    }

    int minDistance(string word1, string word2) {
        int n=word1.size(),m=word2.size();
        int lcs_cnt=lcs(word1,word2,n-1,m-1);
        int ans=n-lcs_cnt+m-lcs_cnt;
        return ans;
    }
};
```

