### Code

```
class Solution {
    public int minDistance(String word1, String word2) {

        int m = word1.length();
        int n = word2.length();

		//use char array instead of charAt method, It eventually increases runtime
        char c1[] = word1.toCharArray();
        char c2[] = word2.toCharArray();

		// 2D array
        int[][] dp = new int[m+1][n+1];


        for(int i=1; i<=m; i++) {
            for(int j=1; j<=n; j++) {
                if(c1[i-1] == c2[j-1]) {
                    dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1] + 1; // if both letter matches increment the count
                }else {
				 // if letter's doesn't match then update current count with max(top, left), top means word1 and left means word2
                    dp[i][j] = Math.max(dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1]);
                }
            }
        }

		// Number of deletions required, dp[m][n] = LCS(word1, word2)
        return (m+n)-2*(dp[m][n]);
    }
}
```

Time Complexity : O(m * n)
Space Complexity : O(m * n)

There are some simlar question which can be solved by same logic'

* [Longest Common Subsequence](https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-common-subsequence/)
* [Longest Palindromic Subsequence](https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-palindromic-subsequence/)

### Code - longest Common Subsequence
