This question is based upon the knowledge of finding longest common subsequences in two string.
Here is my logic.
First we find the length of the ***longest common subsequence***. (https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-common-subsequence/) lets say it is K.
Now , K will be the length of the string word1 and word2 after performing minimum number of deletion operation.
So, Our answer will be  ***word1.size()+word2.size()-2*K***.


Here is my code:-
```
class Solution {
public:
    int dp[501][501]; 
	/*
	DP is used to find K.
	dp[i+1][j+1]->maximum length of the common subsequnce between substring of word1 from index 0 to i and substring of word2 from index 0 to j.
	*/
    int minDistance(string word1, string word2) {
        for(int i=1;i<=word1.size();i++)
        {
            for(int j=1;j<=word2.size();j++)
            {
                dp[i][j]=(word1[i-1]==word2[j-1])?1+dp[i-1][j-1]:max(dp[i-1][j],dp[i][j-1]);
            }
        }
        return word1.size()+word2.size()-2*dp[word1.size()][word2.size()];
    }
};
