**EXPLANATION:** 

The idea is to find the length of the longest common subsequence and subtracting it with the length of both the strings to get the number of characters to be deleted.

Let the length of s1 is m and length of s2 is n then
ans  =( s1 - lcs_len) + (s2 - lcs_len)
ans = s1 + s2 - 2 lcs_len

**1. Recursion
CODE:**

	// Recursion *** Will Give TLE ***
		int findLCS(int idx1, int idx2, string s, string t) {
			if(idx1 < 0 || idx2 < 0)
				return 0;
			// if characters at indexes are same
			if(s[idx1] == t[idx2])
				return 1 + findLCS(idx1 - 1, idx2 - 1, s, t);
			else 
				return max(findLCS(idx1 - 1, idx2, s, t), findLCS(idx1, idx2 - 1, s, t));
		}
		int minDistance(string word1, string word2) {
			int m = word1.size();
			int n = word2.size();
			int lcs_len = findLCS(m-1, n-1, word1, word2);
			return (m + n) - (2 * lcs_len);
		}

