solutions.content:
*------Please **upvote** if you like the solution and explanation.  Please put your doubt/queries in the comments section below.  I will try my best to answer them.------*

**EXPLANATION:**

This question is an extension of the **Longest Common Subsequence** ([https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-common-subsequence/](http://)) question.

The algorithm for this is simple:

1. Find the LCS of the 2 strings.
2. The characters that are not present in the LCS will be the ones that need to be deleted.
3. Hence, our `answer = Length of word1 + Length of word2 - 2 * Length of LCS`

**Why `2 * Length of LCS`?**
Because we will remove the LCS one time each from both the strings to get the extra characters in that string.

Take **word1 ='sea'** and **word2 = 'eat'**.

The longest common subsequence of the 2 strings will be **'ea'**.  So, if we delete **'s'** from **word1** and **'t'** from **word2**, then the resultant strings will be the same, i.e. the LCS.

So, we have deleted **2** characters in total which we get in a mathematical form as:

```
= Length ('sea') + Length ('eat') - 2 * Length ('ea')
= 3 + 3 - (2 * 2)
= 2
```

**Recursive Approach (TLE):**

```
class Solution {
    public int minDistance (String word1, String word2) {
        int len = Solve (word1, word2, word1.length(), word2.length());
        return (word1.length () + word2.length () - 2*len);
    }

    public int Solve (String s, String t, int i, int j) {
        if (i == 0 || j == 0)
            return 0;
        if (s.charAt (i-1) == t.charAt (j-1))
            return 1 + Solve (s, t, i-1, j-1);
        else
            return Math.max (Solve (s, t, i-1, j), Solve (s, t, i, j-1));
    }
}
```

**Memoization of the Recursive Code (Accepted):**

```
class Solution {
    public int dp [][];

    public int minDistance (String word1, String word2) {
        dp = new int [word1.length() + 1][word2.length() + 1];
        for (int row []: dp)
            Arrays.fill (row, -1);
        int len = Solve (word1, word2, word1.length(), word2.length());
        return (word1.length () + word2.length () - 2*len);
    }

    public int Solve (String s, String t, int i, int j) {
        if (i == 0 || j == 0)
            return 0;
        if (dp [i][j] != -1)
            return dp [i][j];
        if (s.charAt (i-1) == t.charAt (j-1))
            return dp [i][j] = 1 + Solve (s, t, i-1, j-1);
        else
            return dp [i][j] = Math.max (Solve (s, t, i-1, j), Solve (s, t, i, j-1));
    }
}
```

**Tabulation from the Memoized Code (Accepted):**

```
class Solution {
    public int minDistance (String word1, String word2) {
        int N = word1.length ();
        int M = word2.length ();
        int dp [][] = new int [N+1][M+1];
        for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
            for (int j = 1; j <= M; j++) {
                if (word1.charAt (i-1) == word2.charAt (j-1))
                    dp [i][j] = dp [i-1][j-1] + 1;
                else
                    dp [i][j] = Math.max (dp [i-1][j], dp [i][j-1]);
            }
        }
        int LCS = dp [N][M];
        return (N + M - (2 * LCS));
    }
}
```

