# Recursive + memoization

## Complexity
- TC (Time Complexity): The time complexity of the lcs function with memoization is O(m * n), where m and n are the lengths of the input strings. The memoization table, represented by the dp vector, is used to store intermediate results and avoid redundant computations.
- SC (Space Complexity): The space complexity of the LCS function with memoization is O(m * n) because it uses a 2D matrix (DP) to store intermediate results. The size of the matrix is determined by the lengths of the input strings. Additionally, the minDistance function uses the dp matrix, which contributes to the space complexity. However, since the DP matrix is reused for subproblems, the overall space complexity is still O(m * n).


### code 1
```
class Solution {
private:
    int lcs(int m, int n, string s, string t, vector<vector<int>> &dp) {
        if(m == 0 || n == 0) return 0;
        if(dp[m][n] != -1) return dp[m][n];
        if(s[m-1] == t[n-1])
            return dp[m][n] = 1 + lcs(m-1, n-1, s, t, dp);
        return dp[m][n] = max(lcs(m, n-1, s, t, dp), lcs(m-1, n, s, t, dp));
    }
public:
    int minDistance(string word1, string word2) {
        int m=word1.size(), n=word2.size();
        vector<vector<int>> dp(m+1, vector<int>(n+1, -1));
        return m+n-2*lcs(m, n, word1, word2, dp);
    }
};
```

