* Find the length of Largest Common Subsequence among word1 and word2, say the length is "len".
* Calculating the non-common length from both the words ,i.e, word1.size()-len + word2.size()-len, this non-common length is the nothing but the minimum operations required to make both words same.
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minDistance(string word1, string word2) {
        vector<vector<int>> dp(word1.size()+1,vector<int>(word2.size()+1,0));
        for(int i =1;i<word1.size()+1;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<word2.size()+1;j++){
                if(word1[i-1]==word2[j-1]) dp[i][j]=1+dp[i-1][j-1];
                else dp[i][j]=max(dp[i-1][j],dp[i][j-1]);
            }
        }
        int maxx=dp[word1.size()][word2.size()];
		//same as word1.size()-maxx + word2.size()-maxx;
        return (word1.size()+word2.size()-2*maxx);
    }
};
```

